WEBVTT

00:01.569 --> 00:02.170
PREVIOUSLY ON "WHITE COLLAR"...

00:03.371 --> 00:04.805
YOUR DAD TOLD ME
THAT OUR DEPARTMENT

00:04.838 --> 00:06.474
IS FILLED WITH DIRTY COPS
AND THEY SET HIM UP.

00:06.507 --> 00:08.842
AND HE'S RIGHT
ABOUT ONE THING.

00:08.876 --> 00:10.178
THERE ARE DIRTY COPS.

00:10.211 --> 00:12.012
Peter:
SENATOR TERRENCE PRATT.

00:12.046 --> 00:13.747
YOU SAID
PRATT COULD HURT YOU.

00:13.781 --> 00:16.217
MY BRAKES --
I DON'T HAVE MY BRAKES.

00:18.219 --> 00:19.253
YOU NEED
TO LEAVE NEW YORK.

00:19.287 --> 00:21.055
MOZZIE HAS A SAFE HOUSE
OUTSIDE THE CITY.

00:21.089 --> 00:23.891
IT TURNS OUT
THAT EMPLOYER I.D. NUMBER

00:23.924 --> 00:27.027
IS FOR A SECURITY COMPANY
NAMED GRIFFIN-MOORE,

00:27.061 --> 00:29.497
WHICH IS LINKED
TO THE 50th FLOOR

00:29.530 --> 00:31.599
OF THE EMPIRE STATE
BUILDING.

00:31.632 --> 00:35.035
LET'S GET THAT BOX
AND BRING MY FATHER HOME.

00:41.142 --> 00:45.045
Man: 13 BUCKS
FOR AN ICE CREAM?

00:45.079 --> 00:47.215
GLUTEN- AND DAIRY-FREE --
YOU WON'T FIND THAT IN KANSAS.

00:47.248 --> 00:49.016
YES, I WILL.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.418
FORGET IT.

00:50.451 --> 00:52.019
NOTHING LIKE
A HAPPY CUSTOMER.

00:52.052 --> 00:53.687
OOH.
I HAVE TO CHANGE MY PRICES.

00:53.721 --> 00:55.623
THE TOURISTS
ARE STILL BOTHERING ME.

00:55.656 --> 00:57.258
MAKES IT TOUGH
TO DO RECON.

00:57.291 --> 00:58.392
SO, WHERE WERE WE?

00:58.426 --> 00:59.560
ON THE 50th FLOOR.

00:59.593 --> 01:01.695
BY "WE," OF COURSE,
I MEANT "ME,"

01:01.729 --> 01:03.697
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T GET
OFF-LEASH.

01:03.731 --> 01:06.767
IT'S CASING AN OFFICE.
I THINK YOU CAN HANDLE IT, MOZ.

01:06.800 --> 01:08.602
OKAY,
THEN YOU MAN THE CART.

01:08.636 --> 01:10.771
NO, I CAN'T STICK AROUND
THAT LONG.

01:10.804 --> 01:12.406
PETER'S CHECKING
MY TRACKING DATA.

01:12.440 --> 01:14.275
WE CAN'T GIVE HIM
ANY REASON TO BELIEVE

01:14.308 --> 01:16.310
THAT WE KNOW WHERE ELLEN
HID THE EVIDENCE.

01:16.344 --> 01:18.312
I GOT
A GOOD THING GOING HERE.

01:18.346 --> 01:20.948
OH.
I HAD A GOOD THING GOING HERE.

01:20.981 --> 01:22.816
Neal:
MOZZIE HAS A PERMIT.

01:22.850 --> 01:23.784
I'M SURE.

01:23.817 --> 01:25.719
I'LL TAKE A PISTACHIO,
PLEASE.

01:25.753 --> 01:27.888
13 -- 15 BUCKS.

01:27.921 --> 01:29.557
I SHOULD ARREST YOU
FOR YOUR PRICES.

01:29.590 --> 01:32.126
FOR AN OFFICER OF THE LAW,
IT'S ON THE HOUSE.

01:32.160 --> 01:33.261
THAT'S BRIBERY.

01:33.294 --> 01:35.563
THEN PAY.

01:35.596 --> 01:37.698
SO, THIS IS WHERE YOU SET UP
YOUR RECON, HUH?

01:39.767 --> 01:41.269
OH, THAT'S GOOD.

01:41.302 --> 01:42.736
MMM.

01:42.770 --> 01:44.138
YOU BELIEVE ELLEN
HID THE EVIDENCE

01:44.172 --> 01:46.106
ON THE 50th FLOOR, RIGHT?

01:47.208 --> 01:50.344
PETER, THERE'S NO NEED FOR YOU
TO GET INVOLVED IN THIS.

01:50.378 --> 01:53.113
NEAL.
I WISH I COULD TELL YOU MORE,
BUT I CAN'T.

01:53.147 --> 01:55.783
YOU CAN'T BECAUSE ELIZABETH
TOLD YOU NOT TO.

01:55.816 --> 01:57.117
ELIZABETH TOLD YOU?

01:57.151 --> 01:58.486
COME ON.

02:00.221 --> 02:03.591
SCRAM.
JUST 17 BUCKS A SCOOP!

02:03.624 --> 02:05.826
YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND
THE POSITION I WAS IN --

02:05.859 --> 02:07.027
YOU WERE IN THE HOSPITAL,

02:07.060 --> 02:08.662
ELIZABETH WAS WORRIED
ABOUT YOU --

02:08.696 --> 02:12.200
UNTIL SHE REALIZED THAT FORCING
YOU TO KEEP A SECRET FROM ME

02:12.233 --> 02:14.668
WASN'T GONNA MAKE THE SITUATION
ANY SAFER.

02:14.702 --> 02:16.204
HOW LONG HAVE YOU KNOWN?

02:16.237 --> 02:17.205
SINCE THE ACCIDENT.

02:17.238 --> 02:18.472
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:18.506 --> 02:21.041
I ACTUALLY THOUGHT
I WAS AHEAD OF YOU THIS TIME.

02:21.074 --> 02:24.512
GETTING THAT EVIDENCE ISN'T ONLY
ABOUT VINDICATING YOUR FATHER.

02:24.545 --> 02:27.014
IT'S ABOUT BRINGING PRATT
TO JUSTICE.

02:27.047 --> 02:30.218
HE FORCED HUGHES OUT OF THE FBI
TO KEEP THAT BOX HIDDEN.

02:30.251 --> 02:32.553
I WANT TO SEE
WHAT'S INSIDE IT.

02:32.586 --> 02:36.023
AND WE'RE GONNA FIND IT.

02:36.056 --> 02:37.124
Callaway:
FOR THOSE OF YOU

02:37.157 --> 02:39.126
THAT I HAVE NOT HAD
THE GOOD FORTUNE OF MEETING,

02:39.159 --> 02:40.861
MY NAME IS AMANDA CALLAWAY.

02:40.894 --> 02:41.962
DID WE MISS SOMETHING?

02:41.995 --> 02:43.364
AND I AM
VERY EXCITED TO...
[ SIGHS ]

02:43.397 --> 02:47.335
AMANDA CALLAWAY -- RAN THE
ATLANTA WHITE COLLAR DIVISION.

02:47.368 --> 02:48.969
SHE'S REPLACING HUGHES?

02:49.002 --> 02:51.339
THERE WERE A LOT OF PEOPLE
AHEAD OF HER ON THE LIST.

02:51.372 --> 02:53.341
AND NEW YORK'S A BIG STEP UP
FROM ATLANTA.

02:56.344 --> 02:58.479
[ SIGHS ] AFTER YOU.
I LOVED ATLANTA.

02:58.512 --> 03:02.149
I REALLY DID,
BUT ATLANTA IS NO NEW YORK.

03:02.182 --> 03:05.052
AND I KNOW THAT THERE ARE
A LOT OF CASE LOADS...

03:05.085 --> 03:06.153
SHE WAS ASKING FOR YOU.

03:06.186 --> 03:07.321
IN A GOOD WAY?

03:07.355 --> 03:08.556
HARD TO TELL.

03:08.589 --> 03:10.991
Callaway: I CAN NEVER REPLACE
AGENT HUGHES.

03:11.024 --> 03:12.059
I DON'T WANT TO.

03:12.092 --> 03:14.161
I WILL RUN THIS DIVISION
DIFFERENTLY.

03:14.194 --> 03:20.200
I PLAN ON TAKING
A MORE INVOLVED APPROACH.
UH-OH.

03:20.234 --> 03:22.202
WE WILL MAKE
NEW YORK WHITE COLLAR

03:22.236 --> 03:24.272
THE PRIDE OF THE BUREAU
ONCE AGAIN.

03:24.305 --> 03:25.573
I DON'T LIKE HER.
SHH.

03:25.606 --> 03:27.241
THANK YOU.

03:27.275 --> 03:29.410
[ APPLAUSE ]

03:31.579 --> 03:33.347
THAT SHOULD BE YOU,
PETER.

03:33.381 --> 03:35.383
YOU SHOULD BE LEADING
WHITE COLLAR.

03:35.416 --> 03:36.183
[ SCOFFS ]

03:36.216 --> 03:38.586
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.

03:38.619 --> 03:40.053
THEY'RE RIGHT.

03:40.087 --> 03:42.956
WELL, THE BUREAU CHIEFS KNOW I
LOVE THE FIELD MORE THAN A DESK.

03:42.990 --> 03:46.360
AND BESIDES, THEY CAN'T LET MY
LITTLE JAUNT TO CAPE VERDE GO.

03:46.394 --> 03:49.229
WHERE, BY THE WAY, YOU CAPTURED
ONE OF THEIR MOST WANTED.

03:49.263 --> 03:51.365
WELL,
AFTER MY DEMOTION TO EVIDENCE,

03:51.399 --> 03:53.567
I'M JUST HAPPY TO BE
IN THE DIVISION.

03:53.601 --> 03:54.568
Callaway: AGENT BURKE.

03:54.602 --> 03:58.071
AGENT CALLAWAY,
CONGRATULATIONS.

03:58.105 --> 03:59.373
OH, MY GOSH.

03:59.407 --> 04:00.574
I WAS SO HAPPY TO HEAR

04:00.608 --> 04:02.610
THAT YOU WERE STILL HERE
AT NEW YORK WHITE COLLAR.

04:02.643 --> 04:03.877
13 YEARS.

04:03.911 --> 04:05.112
THAT'S AMAZING.

04:05.145 --> 04:06.480
NEAL CAFFREY.
A PLEASURE.

04:06.514 --> 04:08.949
OH, THE PLEASURE IS ALL MINE,
AGENT CALLAWAY.

04:08.982 --> 04:10.384
THANK YOU.

04:10.418 --> 04:11.985
AND WHEN I HEARD
ABOUT THE OPENING HERE,

04:12.019 --> 04:13.120
I RESEARCHED YOUR DIVISION

04:13.153 --> 04:14.722
AND FOUND OUT YOU GUYS
REALLY GET IT DONE.

04:14.755 --> 04:16.990
IN NO SMALL PART
DUE TO REESE HUGHES.

04:17.024 --> 04:17.958
MM.

04:17.991 --> 04:19.327
HE WAS
A VERY SUPPORTIVE BOSS.

04:19.360 --> 04:21.329
YEAH, I NOTICED.
I LIKE RESULTS.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.331
SPEAKING OF WHICH,
I LIKE TO GET THEM ABOVE BOARD,

04:23.364 --> 04:26.600
SO LET'S KEEP THAT IN MIND
WITH YOUR NEXT CASE.

04:26.634 --> 04:27.935
WHICH CASE IS THAT?

04:27.968 --> 04:30.504
WELL, YOU TWO HAVE A KNACK
FOR CLOSING ART-FORGERY CASES,

04:30.538 --> 04:32.239
AND THERE HAVE BEEN
SOME SUSPICIONS

04:32.272 --> 04:34.074
ABOUT
THE NEW BERNINI DISCOVERY.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.176
THAT'S A MULTI-MILLION DOLLAR
SCULPTURE.

04:36.209 --> 04:37.244
AND IF IT'S FAKE --

04:37.277 --> 04:38.412
WE CAN BUST THE SELLER,

04:38.446 --> 04:40.914
HAVE A QUICK, HIGH-PROFILE WIN
RIGHT OUT OF THE GATE.

04:40.948 --> 04:42.450
IT'S A WONDERFUL WAY
TO SHOW THE BUREAU

04:42.483 --> 04:44.117
THAT THIS DIVISION
IS BACK ON TRACK.

04:44.151 --> 04:45.519
DIDN'T THINK
WE WERE OFF TRACK.

04:45.553 --> 04:48.055
WELL, SOMEBODY DID,
OR ELSE I WOULDN'T BE HERE.

04:51.392 --> 04:52.760
[ SIGHS ]

04:52.793 --> 04:54.928
DID YOU MENTION
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING

04:54.962 --> 04:56.096
IN YOUR FILE ON PRATT?

04:56.129 --> 04:57.798
NO. I LEFT IT
OUT OF THE REPORT.

04:57.831 --> 05:00.634
YOU'RE WORRIED CALLAWAY MIGHT BE
CONNECTED TO THE SENATOR?

05:00.668 --> 05:02.269
WELL,
SHE WAS NICE TO ME.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.872
WHEN PEOPLE ARE NICE, THEY'RE
USUALLY WORKING AN ANGLE.

05:06.507 --> 05:07.475
WHAT?

05:07.508 --> 05:09.009
I'LL LOOK INTO CALLAWAY.

05:09.042 --> 05:10.277
IN THE MEANTIME,

05:10.310 --> 05:13.313
LET'S JUST TRY AND GET HER
THAT QUICK WIN SHE ASKED FOR.

05:16.917 --> 05:18.452
[ French accent ]
MONSIEUR CAFFREY.

05:18.486 --> 05:20.320
Neal:
[ Laughing ] HENRI.
BONJOUR.

05:20.354 --> 05:22.656
[ BOTH SPEAKING FRENCH ]

05:24.725 --> 05:27.395
AH, THERE'S A HILLSIDE VILLAGE
IN THE FRENCH RIVIERA

05:27.428 --> 05:28.562
KNOWN FOR SCULPTURE, AND --

05:28.596 --> 05:30.464
YOU'RE OLD FRIENDS --
I GET IT.

05:30.498 --> 05:31.331
PETER BURKE, HIS HANDLER.

05:31.365 --> 05:34.167
Leslie: SO,
YOU THINK IT'S REAL?

05:34.201 --> 05:35.335
SCUFF MARKS HERE.

05:35.369 --> 05:37.471
Peter:
THEY LOOK LIKE ROPE BURNS.

05:37.505 --> 05:39.740
YEAH, COTTON-BRAIDED ROPE
WAS THE PREFERRED METHOD

05:39.773 --> 05:42.309
TO PULLEY AND MOVE SCULPTURE
DURING THE NAPOLEONIC WAR.

05:42.342 --> 05:44.512
THERE'S ADDED PLASTER
IN THE PLINTH.

05:44.545 --> 05:46.346
Neal:
BERNINI DID THAT HIMSELF

05:46.380 --> 05:48.215
WHEN HIS PATRON,
MARCANTONIO BORGHESE,

05:48.248 --> 05:51.218
MOVED THE PIECE
TO A LARGER ENTRYWAY...

05:51.251 --> 05:54.922
IN HIS HOME.

05:54.955 --> 05:56.490
EXCELLENT.

05:56.524 --> 05:59.460
NEAL,
YOU CAN BROWSE WHEN WE'RE DONE.

06:03.363 --> 06:06.667
WHAT SOLD ME WAS THE SEAL
ON THE 1842 SHIPPING ORDERS

06:06.700 --> 06:08.335
FROM THE PORT OF BORDEAUX --

06:08.368 --> 06:11.238
THAT RED PIGMENT
IS IMPOSSIBLE TO FIND TODAY.

06:11.271 --> 06:13.006
TRUST ME.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.374
AS FAR AS THE AESTHETIC,

06:14.408 --> 06:16.376
BERNINI WAS THE FIRST
AND ONLY ARTIST OF HIS TIME

06:16.410 --> 06:18.679
TO EXPLORE THE IDEA
OF METAMORPHOSIS IN MARBLE.

06:18.712 --> 06:20.581
THIS IS
THE REAL APHRODITE.

06:20.614 --> 06:21.782
EXCELLENT. THEN --

06:21.815 --> 06:23.584
AS FOR THE ONE
OVER HERE --

06:23.617 --> 06:25.519
AH, THE DUBOIS.

06:25.553 --> 06:27.455
"HAND OVER HAND" --

06:27.488 --> 06:30.357
ONE OF THE FOUR REMAINING PIECES
IN HIS CATALOG.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.793
YEAH, IT JUST SOLD AT AUCTION
LAST WEEK FOR $6.5 MILLION.

06:32.826 --> 06:33.927
IT WAS.

06:33.961 --> 06:38.398
YEAH. THEY'RE GONNA WANT
THEIR MONEY BACK.

06:38.432 --> 06:40.434
IT'S A FAKE.

07:09.429 --> 07:12.933
WE ARE THE EXCLUSIVE DEALERS
OF OLIVIER DUBOIS' WORK.

07:12.966 --> 07:14.001
MM.

07:14.034 --> 07:16.670
THIS PIECE HAS ALREADY BEEN
AUTHENTICATED AND SOLD.

07:16.704 --> 07:19.172
THAT DOESN'T MAKE IT
ANY LESS OF A FORGERY.

07:19.206 --> 07:22.476
WHY DON'T YOU EXPLAIN EXACTLY
WHY YOU THINK IT'S A FAKE?

07:22.510 --> 07:25.779
WELL, TECHNICALLY, ALL
THE STYLE ELEMENTS ARE THERE.

07:25.813 --> 07:27.981
I MEAN,
IT'S A BRILLIANT FORGERY --

07:28.015 --> 07:28.982
IT'S TOO GOOD.

07:29.016 --> 07:31.652
IT'S SUBTLE, BUT THESE LINES
WHERE THE HANDS MEET

07:31.685 --> 07:34.021
FEEL EVER SO SLIGHTLY
FORCED TO DIMENSION,

07:34.054 --> 07:37.090
WHERE A DUBOIS WOULD FLOW
MORE EASILY, LESS EXACT.

07:37.124 --> 07:38.926
DUBOIS MAY HAVE CHANGED
TECHNIQUES

07:38.959 --> 07:41.962
JUST AS HE SHIFTED MOTIFS
IN HIS FINAL YEARS.

07:41.995 --> 07:44.131
EVERY DUBOIS CONTAINS
HIS UNIQUE SIGNATURE --

07:44.164 --> 07:46.600
A HAND-WRITTEN NOTE INSERTED
INTO THE CENTER OF THE MARBLE.

07:46.634 --> 07:48.001
WHAT'S ON IT?

07:48.035 --> 07:50.671
WELL, SUPPOSEDLY, HE EXPOSES
THE HEART OF THE PIECE,

07:50.704 --> 07:51.939
BUT NO ONE KNOWS EXACTLY.

07:51.972 --> 07:54.307
THAT'S PART OF THE MYSTIQUE
OF HIS WORK.

07:54.341 --> 07:57.945
WE VERIFIED
WITH X-RAY DIFFRACTION.
AH.

07:57.978 --> 08:00.280
A SCROLL IS INSIDE.

08:00.313 --> 08:02.382
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH CHICKEN SEXERS?

08:02.415 --> 08:04.017
NO,
I DON'T BELIEVE I AM.

08:04.051 --> 08:07.320
BABY CHICKENS NEED TO BE SORTED
INTO MALES AND FEMALES.

08:07.354 --> 08:08.822
THE SORTERS
ARE CALLED SEXERS.

08:08.856 --> 08:11.792
THE ONLY PROBLEM IS
BABY CHICKS LOOK IDENTICAL.

08:11.825 --> 08:13.326
THIS WILL LOOP
BACK TO THE DUBOIS?

08:13.360 --> 08:15.996
THE JAPANESE DEVELOPED
A FOOL-PROOF TECHNIQUE,

08:16.029 --> 08:18.666
BUT THE ONLY WAY TO TEACH IT
IS TO PICK UP A CHICK

08:18.699 --> 08:21.902
AND PLACE IT IN EITHER THE MALE
OR THE FEMALE BIN.
NEAL.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.537
NOW, AT FIRST
THEY'RE JUST GUESSING.

08:23.571 --> 08:25.072
A TEACHER WILL STAND BEHIND
A STUDENT AND SAY "YES"

08:25.105 --> 08:26.540
EACH TIME
THEY GUESS CORRECTLY.

08:26.574 --> 08:28.175
BUT AFTER A FEW MONTHS,
A STUDENT IS ABLE

08:28.208 --> 08:30.911
TO SORT THE CHICKS CORRECTLY
100% OF THE TIME,

08:30.944 --> 08:33.647
AND TO THIS DAY, NO ONE
IS ABLE TO ARTICULATE WHY.

08:33.681 --> 08:36.750
THERE IS A SCIENTIFIC BASIS
FOR INSTINCT.

08:36.784 --> 08:38.919
AND AS DUBOIS-ESQUE
AS THIS SEEMS,

08:38.952 --> 08:40.220
IT'S NOT A DUBOIS.

08:40.253 --> 08:42.222
WHO SOLD YOU THE PIECE?

08:42.255 --> 08:44.592
DUBOIS' PROTéGé,
J.B. BELLMIERE.

08:44.625 --> 08:46.827
UNTIL DUBOIS' DEATH
LAST YEAR,

08:46.860 --> 08:50.030
A MAN NAMED J.B. BELLMIERE
WORKED AS HIS APPRENTICE.

08:50.063 --> 08:51.932
HE'S THE MAN WHO AUTHENTICATES
DUBOIS' WORK.

08:51.965 --> 08:55.068
HE'S CONSIDERED
THE ULTIMATE AUTHORITY.

08:55.102 --> 08:56.837
Peter: AGENT CALLAWAY.

08:56.870 --> 09:00.040
AGENT BURKE. PLEASE,
DON'T LET ME INTERRUPT YOU.

09:00.073 --> 09:03.076
Diana: PETER WAS JUST EXPLAINING
THAT IF THE DUBOIS IS A FORGERY,

09:03.110 --> 09:05.245
THEN BELLMIERE WOULD BE
OUR PRIME SUSPECT.

09:05.278 --> 09:06.880
I SEE.
AND THIS IS BASED

09:06.914 --> 09:10.517
ON CAFFREY'S HIGHLY CRITICAL
CHICKEN SEXER THEORY?

09:10.550 --> 09:12.085
HE...
MAY HAVE MENTIONED THAT.

09:12.119 --> 09:13.020
[ SNIFFS ]

09:13.053 --> 09:15.088
AT THE TIME
OF DUBOIS' DEATH,

09:15.122 --> 09:17.691
THERE WERE FOUR SCULPTURES
IN HIS CATALOG

09:17.725 --> 09:19.559
THAT HAD NEVER GONE
TO MARKET.

09:19.593 --> 09:21.729
"HAND OVER HAND"
IS THE FIRST ONE TO SURFACE.

09:21.762 --> 09:23.030
ARE YOU SUGGESTING
THAT BELLMIERE,

09:23.063 --> 09:25.098
AS HIS APPRENTICE,
COULD HAVE FORGED IT?
I AM.

09:25.132 --> 09:26.099
INTERESTING THEORY.

09:26.133 --> 09:28.301
PETER,
WHEN YOU'RE FINISHED HERE,

09:28.335 --> 09:30.237
WILL YOU SEE ME
IN MY OFFICE?

09:30.270 --> 09:31.905
OF COURSE.

09:31.939 --> 09:34.174
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

09:36.744 --> 09:38.111
HEY.
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

09:38.145 --> 09:41.214
MOZZIE'S SAFEHOUSE IS A 10-BY-10
UNDERGROUND BOMB SHELTER

09:41.248 --> 09:42.750
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE WOODS

09:42.783 --> 09:45.552
SURROUNDED BY A PIG FARM
AND A BOG.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.621
I TAKE IT YOU'RE READY
FOR A CHANGE OF VENUE?

09:47.655 --> 09:49.322
I'm ready for my freedom.
Any updates?

09:49.356 --> 09:50.758
YEAH,
WE'RE GETTING CLOSE.

09:50.791 --> 09:52.893
HOW CLOSE?
WEEKS? DAYS?

09:52.926 --> 09:54.094
I can't say yet.

09:54.127 --> 09:56.930
LISTEN,
PETER'S INVOLVED NOW.

09:56.964 --> 09:58.098
THAT DOESN'T SOUND GOOD.

09:58.131 --> 09:59.166
WELL, IT IS.

09:59.199 --> 10:01.134
LISTEN, I SHOULD BE THERE.
LET ME HELP.

10:01.168 --> 10:02.235
NO, WE CAN'T RISK IT.

10:02.269 --> 10:03.937
WE GOT A NEW BOSS
AT THE BUREAU --

10:03.971 --> 10:05.505
SHE'S KEEPING A CLOSE EYE
ON US.

10:05.538 --> 10:07.641
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
THE MINUTE WE LOCATE THE BOX.

10:07.675 --> 10:09.042
Do it soon.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.450
I WANT YOU TO MOVE OFF
THE BELLMIERE CASE.

10:17.484 --> 10:18.485
WHAT? WHY?

10:18.518 --> 10:21.154
THERE'S JUST NOT ENOUGH
HARD EVIDENCE.

10:21.188 --> 10:22.222
YET.

10:22.255 --> 10:24.124
LOOK, IF YOU WANT TO DIG
INTO THIS IN YOUR OWN TIME,

10:24.157 --> 10:25.125
FEEL FREE.

10:25.158 --> 10:26.193
JUST DON'T DO IT
ON THE BUREAU'S.

10:26.226 --> 10:28.128
IF NEAL'S RIGHT --
AND I TRUST HIS HUNCH --

10:28.161 --> 10:30.163
WE'RE DEALING
WITH A WORLD-CLASS FORGER.

10:30.197 --> 10:31.699
BUT WE HAVE
A GROWING STACK OF CASES

10:31.732 --> 10:33.133
WITH CONCLUSIVE DATA
WE CAN WORK.

10:33.166 --> 10:36.937
YOU AND NEAL ARE AN IMPRESSIVE
TEAM, BUT YOU'RE TOO IMPULSIVE.

10:36.970 --> 10:39.707
FOCUS YOUR ENERGY
ON CASES WE CAN CLOSE.

10:39.740 --> 10:43.110
EFFICIENCY IS
OUR MOST IMPORTANT TOOL.
I GET IT.

10:43.143 --> 10:45.946
WE WANT A QUICK, HIGH-PROFILE
WIN TO IMPRESS THE BUREAU.

10:45.979 --> 10:47.014
THERE YOU GO.

10:50.417 --> 10:52.720
Elizabeth:
YOU'RE GONNA DROP THE CASE?

10:52.753 --> 10:54.722
NO, I CAN'T LET
A MULTI-MILLION DOLLAR FORGER GO

10:54.755 --> 10:56.824
JUST BECAUSE IT MIGHT NOT BE
AN EASY WIN.

10:56.857 --> 10:59.059
THAT'S WHY THEY
SHOULD HAVE GIVEN YOU THE JOB.

10:59.092 --> 11:00.393
THEY'RE
GONNA REALIZE THAT.

11:00.427 --> 11:02.295
I DON'T WANT IT.

11:02.329 --> 11:04.131
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN NICE
TO BE ASKED.

11:04.164 --> 11:06.266
YEAH.

11:08.601 --> 11:10.303
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

11:10.337 --> 11:11.905
[ SILVERWARE CLATTERS ]

11:16.009 --> 11:17.177
HEY, NEAL.
HEY.

11:17.210 --> 11:18.078
COME ON IN.

11:18.111 --> 11:19.479
WHAT WAS SO URGENT?

11:19.512 --> 11:22.082
WELL, HOW WOULD YOU
LIKE TO MEET THE MAN

11:22.115 --> 11:24.351
BEHIND THAT MAGNIFICENT FORGERY
YOU SPOTTED?

11:24.384 --> 11:26.353
YOU FOUND MORE INFORMATION
ON BELLMIERE?

11:26.386 --> 11:29.089
YEAH.
HIS REAL NAME'S JEFF BLATNIK.

11:29.122 --> 11:31.258
WELL, YOU CAN'T FAULT HIM
FOR CHANGING HIS NAME.

11:31.291 --> 11:32.860
A LOT OF ARTISTS
CHANGE THEIR NAME.

11:32.893 --> 11:34.161
SO DO CON ARTISTS.

11:34.194 --> 11:36.529
I'D BUY A BELLMIERE
OVER A BLATNIK --

11:36.563 --> 11:38.065
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING.

11:38.098 --> 11:40.768
BUT HE DIDN'T SELL A BELLMIERE.
HE SOLD A DUBOIS.

11:40.801 --> 11:43.036
MM, TRUE.

12:05.125 --> 12:08.128
THE SECOND DUBOIS
IN HIS CATALOG...

12:08.161 --> 12:11.231
OR IS IT?

12:11.264 --> 12:12.699
THAT'S SO CLOSE.

12:12.732 --> 12:15.235
BELLMIERE HAS
AN INCREDIBLE EYE.

12:15.268 --> 12:19.239
IT'S JUST --
IT'S NOT A DUBOIS.

12:21.641 --> 12:23.410
HEY.

12:23.443 --> 12:24.812
HMM?

12:24.845 --> 12:26.213
WHILE YOU LOOK FOR J.B.,

12:26.246 --> 12:28.281
WHY DON'T I FIND OUT
WHAT HIS STUDENTS HAVE TO SAY?

12:28.315 --> 12:29.682
GO.

12:39.426 --> 12:41.061
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]

12:41.094 --> 12:43.230
ORIGINAL.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.565
CONCEPTUAL.

12:45.598 --> 12:48.601
I'M GONNA SAY THE WIRES
REPRESENT INDUSTRY --

12:48.635 --> 12:51.171
AN ENDLESS LOOP
SPIRALING DOWNWARD.

12:51.204 --> 12:52.272
YOU GET ME.

12:52.305 --> 12:54.141
[ CHUCKLES ] I'VE BEEN FOLLOWING
THE BELLMIERE SCHOOL

12:54.174 --> 12:55.242
FOR A WHILE.

12:55.275 --> 12:56.109
NEAL.

12:56.143 --> 12:57.110
NATASHA.

12:57.144 --> 12:59.312
I RUN THE HAVERSHAM GALLERY
IN PORTLAND.

12:59.346 --> 13:01.248
OH,
I'LL...GET MR. BELLMIERE.

13:01.281 --> 13:02.315
OH, IN A LITTLE BIT.

13:02.349 --> 13:04.284
I WANT TO SEE
IF ANY OF THE OTHER PIECES

13:04.317 --> 13:05.485
SPEAK TO ME
LIKE YOURS DOES.

13:07.988 --> 13:09.957
Bellmiere:
KNOCK IT OVER.

13:09.990 --> 13:11.291
COME ON! BREAK IT!

13:11.324 --> 13:12.792
IT EITHER WORKS,
OR IT DOESN'T.

13:12.826 --> 13:15.128
LAST CHANCE.

13:26.239 --> 13:27.507
NOW YOU CAN START FRESH.

13:27.540 --> 13:29.542
[ CRIES ]

13:32.645 --> 13:35.382
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:35.415 --> 13:36.950
DUBOIS TAUGHT ME THAT.

13:36.984 --> 13:37.951
MM.

13:37.985 --> 13:39.987
DESTRUCTION IS
PART OF CREATION.

13:42.422 --> 13:43.323
WHO ARE YOU?

13:43.356 --> 13:47.627
I'M PETER BURKE, FBI.
WE NEED YOUR HELP.

13:47.660 --> 13:49.329
LET'S CUT THROUGH THE FACADE,
AGENT BURKE.

13:49.362 --> 13:50.830
YOU'RE HERE
BECAUSE YOU WANT TO KNOW

13:50.864 --> 13:53.300
IF THE DUBOIS THAT I SOLD
TO THE TIBEDAUX IS A FORGERY.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.869
ANY INFORMATION YOU HAVE
ON THE PIECE WOULD HELP.

13:55.903 --> 13:57.404
WHO SUGGESTED
IT WAS A FAKE?

13:57.437 --> 13:58.906
ONE OF THEIR EXPERTS.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.307
"EXPERTS."

14:00.340 --> 14:02.709
I AM THE EXPERT ON DUBOIS.

14:02.742 --> 14:03.810
OF COURSE.

14:03.843 --> 14:05.478
THE COMPLAINT WAS

14:05.512 --> 14:09.249
THAT SOMEHOW THE LINES LACKED
A CERTAIN SUBTLETY

14:09.282 --> 14:11.184
FOUND
IN OTHER DUBOIS PIECES.

14:14.754 --> 14:17.724
"HAND OVER HAND"
MAY NOT BE AS INSPIRED

14:17.757 --> 14:19.859
AS SOME OF HIS EARLIER WORKS,

14:19.893 --> 14:22.930
BUT PERHAPS THAT'S WHY
HE GAVE IT TO ME.

14:22.963 --> 14:25.698
HE GAVE YOU
A $6.5 MILLION STATUE?

14:25.732 --> 14:28.335
I GAVE HIM 10 YEARS.

14:28.368 --> 14:30.237
WHERE CAN I SEE
SOME OF MR. BELLMIERE'S WORK?

14:30.270 --> 14:32.405
OH, HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY
ON DISPLAY.

14:32.439 --> 14:33.540
REALLY? NOTHING?

14:33.573 --> 14:35.842
WELL, HE'S...BEEN SPENDING
A LOT OF TIME

14:35.875 --> 14:39.579
IN HIS PRIVATE WORKSPACE --
OFF THE HALLWAY.

14:39.612 --> 14:41.514
YOU SEEN
WHAT HE'S BEEN WORKING ON?

14:41.548 --> 14:43.450
OH, NO ONE HAS.
HE WORKS ALONE.

14:43.483 --> 14:44.351
IT'S HIS PROCESS.

14:44.384 --> 14:45.518
OH.

14:45.552 --> 14:47.287
MAYBE I CAN CONVINCE HIM
TO GIVE ME A SNEAK PEAK.

14:47.320 --> 14:48.655
GOOD LUCK.
THANKS.

14:59.099 --> 15:04.104
OUT OF CURIOSITY,
WHAT DOES YOUR WORK SELL FOR?

15:04.137 --> 15:07.307
I'M TAKING MY TIME TO DEFINE
WHAT MAKES A BELLMIERE.

15:07.340 --> 15:09.242
SO, YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
ON THE MARKET, HUH?

15:10.410 --> 15:13.346
MM. THANK YOU.

15:39.806 --> 15:41.808
HEY.
HEY.

15:41.841 --> 15:43.843
DID YOU SEE
ANY OF BELLMIERE'S WORK?

15:43.876 --> 15:46.146
YEAH, TWO PARTIALLY COMPLETED
SCULPTURES.

15:46.179 --> 15:49.016
OH. HE REALLY IS TAKING HIS TIME
TO FIND HIS OWN VISION.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.450
IS THAT
WHAT HE TOLD YOU?

15:50.483 --> 15:52.619
OH, "SOME IDEAS
COME FULLY FORMED.

15:52.652 --> 15:53.853
OTHERS TAKE YEARS."

15:53.886 --> 15:56.623
WELL, HE'S FULLY FORMED ONES
COME FROM DUBOIS.

15:56.656 --> 15:59.292
SO, HE'S FORGING
THE LAST TWO CATALOG PIECES.

15:59.326 --> 16:02.662
THE SAME RARE MARBLE,
TECHNIQUE, STYLE.

16:02.695 --> 16:05.465
WELL, WE CAN'T MAKE A BUST UNTIL
HE TRIES TO SELL ONE OF THEM.

16:05.498 --> 16:06.933
BELLMIERE'S
ALREADY MADE MILLIONS

16:06.966 --> 16:08.135
OFF "HAND OVER HAND."

16:08.168 --> 16:09.836
HE COULD SIT ON THE OTHER THREE
FOR YEARS

16:09.869 --> 16:11.804
WHILE THEIR VALUE
SKYROCKETS.

16:11.838 --> 16:15.442
[ SIGHS ] IS THERE ANY WAY
HE'D WANT TO SELL THEM EARLIER?

16:15.475 --> 16:17.377
I COULD ENCOURAGE HIM.

16:17.410 --> 16:19.479
BUT I'M GONNA NEED
ABOUT 500 POUNDS OF MARBLE.

16:19.512 --> 16:21.181
ALL RIGHT.

17:07.360 --> 17:09.362
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

17:09.396 --> 17:11.398
ENTREZ, MOZ.

17:19.872 --> 17:20.907
HEY.

17:20.940 --> 17:22.575
GOOD TO SEE YOU, TOO,
KID.

17:29.916 --> 17:30.683
LOOK, IT'S TOO RISKY
FOR YOU TO BE HERE.

17:31.884 --> 17:34.020
I CAN'T TAKE MOZZIE'S SAFEHOUSE
ANYMORE.

17:34.053 --> 17:34.954
WHY?

17:34.987 --> 17:37.757
HE'S A VERY WEIRD DUDE.

17:37.790 --> 17:40.193
YEAH.

17:40.227 --> 17:42.395
SO,
WHAT AM I LOOKING AT?

17:42.429 --> 17:43.696
DUBOIS' "DEVOLUTION."

17:43.730 --> 17:46.133
I'M SORRY,
BUT YOU GOT TO GO BACK.

17:46.166 --> 17:49.469
LISTEN, YOU'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR THAT EVIDENCE BOX

17:49.502 --> 17:51.538
FOR, WHAT,
THREE MONTHS NOW?

17:51.571 --> 17:53.606
I'VE BEEN AFTER IT
FOR 30 YEARS.

17:53.640 --> 17:54.974
NOW YOU SAY YOU'RE CLOSE.

17:55.007 --> 17:57.710
WHEN WITSEC MOVED ELLEN
TO NEW YORK 12 YEARS AGO,

17:57.744 --> 18:00.213
THEY GAVE HER A JOB
AT A SECURITIES FIRM.

18:00.247 --> 18:02.882
SHE HAD ACCESS TO THE 50th FLOOR
OF THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING

18:02.915 --> 18:04.551
WHILE IT WAS
UNDER RENOVATION.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.052
YOU THINK
SHE PLANTED IT THERE?

18:06.085 --> 18:07.654
MOZ HAS BEEN CASING THE PLACE
ALL DAY.

18:07.687 --> 18:08.755
WE'LL KNOW SOON.

18:08.788 --> 18:11.124
SO...WE WAIT.

18:11.158 --> 18:12.625
YEAH.

18:12.659 --> 18:15.862
WE WAIT.

18:19.031 --> 18:21.568
I'VE HEARD OF DUBOIS.

18:21.601 --> 18:24.737
YEAH, WELL, ONE OF HIS PIECES
JUST SOLD FOR $6.5 MILLION --

18:24.771 --> 18:25.772
IT WAS A FORGERY.

18:25.805 --> 18:26.939
SO,
YOU'RE DOING THIS FOR WORK?

18:26.973 --> 18:29.842
YEAH, I HAVE TO PASS THIS OFF
AS A REAL DUBOIS.

18:29.876 --> 18:31.010
WOW.

18:31.043 --> 18:32.312
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

18:36.115 --> 18:37.150
Hey, Moz.

18:37.184 --> 18:39.852
AS FOND AS I AM
OF THE JAPANESE CULTURE,

18:39.886 --> 18:44.357
I COULD GO THE REST OF MY LIFE
WITHOUT HEARING "CHIIZU" AGAIN.

18:44.391 --> 18:46.259
JAPANESE FOR "SAY CHEESE"?

18:46.293 --> 18:47.660
AMONG OTHER THINGS.

18:47.694 --> 18:48.961
HELLO, MOZZIE.

18:48.995 --> 18:49.829
IS THAT JAMES?

18:49.862 --> 18:51.264
You're on speaker.

18:51.298 --> 18:52.865
JAMES, WHAT HAPPENED?

18:52.899 --> 18:54.667
HE WAS GOING STIR-CRAZY.

18:54.701 --> 18:57.204
AT MY CABIN?
BUT IT'S SO PICTURESQUE.

18:57.237 --> 18:58.971
THERE ARE NO WINDOWS.

18:59.005 --> 19:00.873
INSUFFICIENT MOTIVATION.

19:00.907 --> 19:05.212
HOWEVER, YOUR PREMATURE ARRIVAL
IS ACTUALLY WELL-TIMED.

19:05.245 --> 19:08.848
ME AND MY PHOTOS WILL BE THERE
MOMENTARILY.

19:12.018 --> 19:14.887
NEAL AND I VISITED HIS STUDIO
OFF HOURS --

19:14.921 --> 19:16.055
AS YOU SUGGESTED.

19:16.088 --> 19:17.457
I DID NOT SUGGEST FOR YOU

19:17.490 --> 19:19.726
TO SPEND 15 GRAND
OF THIS DIVISION'S MONEY

19:19.759 --> 19:20.793
ON RARE ITALIAN MARBLE.

19:20.827 --> 19:23.196
THAT WAS WELL WITHIN
MY DISCRETIONARY BUDGET

19:23.230 --> 19:25.665
FOR DEVELOPING
INVESTIGATIONS.

19:25.698 --> 19:28.067
I WILL LOOK INTO
THE DISCRETIONARY BUDGET LATER.

19:28.100 --> 19:30.002
RIGHT NOW,
EXPLAIN THE MARBLE.

19:30.036 --> 19:32.972
WE BELIEVE BELLMIERE IS FORGING
THE REMAINING TWO DUBOIS.

19:33.005 --> 19:34.474
OKAY.

19:34.507 --> 19:35.975
BUT HE COULD SIT ON THEM
FOR YEARS,

19:36.008 --> 19:37.810
SO NEAL IS SCULPTING
ONE OF THE TWO.

19:37.844 --> 19:39.178
ONCE IT'S AUTHENTICATED --

19:39.212 --> 19:40.813
IT'LL DRIVE BELLMIERE CRAZY

19:40.847 --> 19:43.816
BECAUSE IT'LL BE MILLIONS
OF DOLLARS OUT OF HIS POCKET.
RIGHT.

19:43.850 --> 19:46.085
NEAL REACHES OUT TO BELLMIERE,
OFFERS HIS SKILLS,

19:46.118 --> 19:48.087
AND WE DRAW A CONFESSION
FROM COLLUSION.

19:48.120 --> 19:49.856
IT'S RISKY.

19:49.889 --> 19:52.392
IT'S EFFICIENT
AND HIGH-PROFILE.

19:52.425 --> 19:56.596
DID HUGHES AUTHORIZE YOU TO GO
AFTER THESE TYPES OF OPERATIONS?

19:56.629 --> 19:57.730
HE TRUSTED ME.

19:57.764 --> 19:59.266
IT COST HIM HIS JOB.

19:59.299 --> 20:00.867
I LIKE THIS JOB.

20:00.900 --> 20:02.669
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE IT.

20:02.702 --> 20:06.339
REESE DIDN'T LOSE HIS JOB
OVER A $15,000 EXPENSE.

20:06.373 --> 20:07.840
NO, HE LOST IT
BECAUSE HE APPROVED YOU

20:07.874 --> 20:09.542
TO GO AFTER SOMEONE
YOU COULDN'T BEAT.

20:09.576 --> 20:12.945
YOU READ OUR FILE
ON SENATOR PRATT.

20:12.979 --> 20:13.880
I DID.

20:13.913 --> 20:16.283
IS THAT INVESTIGATION
STILL OPEN?

20:19.319 --> 20:21.621
SHE ASKED YOU TO CLOSE THE CASE
AGAINST PRATT?

20:21.654 --> 20:23.590
NO, S CLOSED THE CASE
AGAINST PRATT.

20:23.623 --> 20:25.091
SHE'S GOT TO BE
IN HIS POCKET.

20:25.124 --> 20:26.293
I HAVEN'T FOUND A LINK.

20:26.326 --> 20:27.794
BUT IF YOU WERE
SEXING CHICKENS --

20:27.827 --> 20:29.862
CALLAWAY IS AMBITIOUS
AND PRAGMATIC.

20:29.896 --> 20:32.865
SHE KNOWS THAT OUR INVESTIGATION
INTO PRATT FORCED HUGHES OUT,

20:32.899 --> 20:34.934
SO SHE MAY JUST BE
PROTECTING HER JOB.

20:34.967 --> 20:37.136
SHE'S READING YOUR LOGS
PRETTY CAREFULLY.

20:37.169 --> 20:38.938
YEAH,
IT'S GONNA BE A CHALLENGE

20:38.971 --> 20:40.873
TO KEEP THE EMPIRE STATE
OFF HER RADAR.

20:40.907 --> 20:42.942
ESPECIALLY WITH MY FATHER
BACK IN TOWN.

20:42.975 --> 20:44.711
[ SIGHS ]

20:44.744 --> 20:46.546
SEND HIM BACK --
IMMEDIATELY.

20:46.579 --> 20:47.880
I TRIED.

20:47.914 --> 20:49.148
IF WE FORCE HIM,
HE'LL JUST GO ROGUE,

20:49.181 --> 20:50.983
WHICH WILL BE
EVEN MORE PROBLEMATIC.
[ SIGHS ]

20:51.017 --> 20:53.286
I GUESS THAT ANSWERS
THE AGE-OLD QUESTION

20:53.320 --> 20:56.122
OF NATURE VERSUS NURTURE.

21:05.031 --> 21:08.568
Peter: OUR AUTHENTICATORS
ARE IN DEEP DISCUSSION.

21:08.601 --> 21:10.903
Neal:
THEY BETTER GO FOR IT.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.071
Man:
HAVE YOU SEEN THE PROVENANCE?

21:12.104 --> 21:13.640
WHAT IS BELLMIERE
DOING HERE?

21:13.673 --> 21:15.241
HE WASN'T
SUPPOSED TO SHOW UP

21:15.274 --> 21:17.444
UNTIL AFTER THE PIECE
WAS AUTHENTICATED.

21:17.477 --> 21:19.245
IF HE CLAIMS
IT'S A FRAUD --

21:19.278 --> 21:20.947
HIS WORD MAY SUPERCEDE
THE EXPERTS'.

21:20.980 --> 21:24.016
HE CAN'T SEE YOU.
HE'S GONNA SMELL A SETUP.

21:26.986 --> 21:28.020
LESLIE.

21:28.054 --> 21:29.489
J.B., I DIDN'T WANT TO TROUBLE
YOU WITH THIS

21:29.522 --> 21:30.957
UNTIL WE HAD IT
AUTHENTICATED.

21:30.990 --> 21:33.360
IF A DUBOIS IS COMING TO MARKET,
I KNOW ABOUT IT.

21:33.393 --> 21:34.661
SOMEONE'S CLAIMING

21:34.694 --> 21:35.995
IT'S THE SECOND
OF THE FOUR REMAINING PIECES.

21:36.028 --> 21:38.331
THE EXPLORATION
OF FIGURATIVE TECHNIQUES

21:38.365 --> 21:40.433
WASN'T UNTIL
HE MET HIS FIFTH WIFE.

21:40.467 --> 21:42.669
IT'S HARD TO TELL
FROM THE CATALOG PHOTOS,

21:42.702 --> 21:44.871
BUT IT CERTAINLY TRACKS
WITH THE TIMELINE.

21:44.904 --> 21:46.138
DID YOU CHECK THE PALM?

21:46.172 --> 21:47.374
UNFINISHED.

21:47.407 --> 21:49.509
DUBOIS LEFT THE PALMS UNTOUCHED
IN HIS ABSTRACTIONS.

21:49.542 --> 21:52.011
2004 --
HE MADE NOTHING ELSE THAT YEAR.

21:52.044 --> 21:53.112
AND INSIDE?

21:53.145 --> 21:55.748
THAT'S WHAT CONVINCED US.
WE RAN THE X-RAY.

22:02.822 --> 22:07.159
NO.
THIS IS NOT...A DUBOIS.

22:07.193 --> 22:10.062
IT IS THE DUBOIS.

22:10.096 --> 22:13.866
IT IS THE HEIGHT OF HIS MASTERY
AND HIS SEMINAL WORK.

22:27.380 --> 22:28.347
WHO ARE YOU?

22:36.789 --> 22:37.557
Bellmiere: I'M VERY CURIOUS,
MR. CAFFREY.

22:39.058 --> 22:41.160
HOW DID YOU COME
TO OWN "DEVOLUTION"?

22:41.193 --> 22:42.895
I IMAGINE
MUCH THE SAME WAY

22:42.929 --> 22:45.832
AS YOU CAME TO OWN
THE DUBOIS YOU SOLD LAST WEEK.

22:45.865 --> 22:48.200
YOURS IS A FRAUD.

22:48.234 --> 22:49.702
ARE YOU QUESTIONING
THE EXPERTS?

22:49.736 --> 22:52.238
I WOULDN'T.

22:52.271 --> 22:54.106
THAT WOULD MAKE IT
MUCH MORE DIFFICULT

22:54.140 --> 22:56.008
FOR YOU TO SELL
THE REMAINING THREE --

22:56.042 --> 23:00.680
EXCUSE ME, NOW TWO DUBOISES.

23:00.713 --> 23:02.849
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

23:02.882 --> 23:05.885
THERE IS AN ARRANGEMENT
WHERE WE EACH SELL ONE.

23:05.918 --> 23:08.421
"SISTERS" IS
ALREADY ON DISPLAY IN MY LOFT.

23:08.455 --> 23:09.756
EVERYONE KNOWS THAT.

23:09.789 --> 23:12.892
BUT NO ONE'S SEEN "COURTSHIP"
YET, HAVE THEY?

23:15.962 --> 23:19.799
COME TO MY STUDIO TOMORROW --
2:00.

23:32.144 --> 23:33.813
GOOD INSTINCTS.

23:33.846 --> 23:37.116
YEP.
TRUST THE CHICKEN SEXERS.

23:37.149 --> 23:39.652
AFTERNOON.

23:39.686 --> 23:43.089
YEP. THAT IT IS.

23:43.122 --> 23:44.423
ANY IDEAS ON THE BOX?

23:44.457 --> 23:46.726
WELL,
I'M DEVELOPING A THEORY.

23:46.759 --> 23:49.061
WHEN ELLEN AND I
WERE PARTNERS,

23:49.095 --> 23:51.598
WE BUSTED OUR FAIR SHARE
OF HIDEOUTS.

23:51.631 --> 23:54.567
WHEN IT CAME TO FINDING STASHES,
WE HAD A SAYING --

23:54.601 --> 23:57.436
"WALLS MOVE,
CEILINGS AND FLOORS DON'T."

23:57.470 --> 23:59.238
WELL,
THE FLOORS ARE MARBLE.

23:59.271 --> 24:01.173
YOU THINK SHE HID IT
IN THE CEILING?

24:01.207 --> 24:03.075
WELL,
IF I WAS A BETTING MAN...

24:03.109 --> 24:06.913
ALL YOU GOT TO DO IS SCAN 1,000
SQUARE FEET OF CEILING TILE.

24:06.946 --> 24:09.115
WE'VE NARROWED OUR SEARCH
FROM ALL OF MANHATTAN

24:09.148 --> 24:11.283
TO A CEILING
IN THE CORNER OF A BUILDING.

24:11.317 --> 24:12.351
WE'RE GONNA FIND IT.

24:12.384 --> 24:15.087
OPTIMIST.
AH, GOOD MOOD.

24:15.121 --> 24:16.789
THEY MUST HAVE BOUGHT
YOUR SCULPTURE.

24:16.823 --> 24:18.457
THEY DID.

24:18.491 --> 24:19.592
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

24:19.626 --> 24:22.328
THEY SAID
IT WASN'T A DUBOIS --

24:22.361 --> 24:24.263
IT WAS THE DUBOIS.

24:24.296 --> 24:25.431
YOU'RE KIDDING.

24:25.464 --> 24:27.299
THEY CALLED IT
HIS SEMINAL WORK.

24:27.333 --> 24:31.771
[ Laughing ] I KNEW IT!
ATTABOY!

24:31.804 --> 24:33.205
[ SIGHS ]

24:36.208 --> 24:38.210
FULL DISCLOSURE.

24:43.249 --> 24:45.818
THAT HELPS EXPLAIN WHAT I FOUND
WHILE YOU WERE OUT.

24:45.852 --> 24:47.186
SUCH AS?

24:47.219 --> 24:49.355
OH...

24:49.388 --> 24:51.658
SUCH AS A VAN DYCK...

24:56.228 --> 24:57.363
...AND THIS DEGAS.

24:57.396 --> 24:59.298
THEY'RE FORGERIES.

24:59.331 --> 25:01.333
THEY'RE FLAWLESS.

25:01.367 --> 25:03.936
FLAWLESS.

25:05.204 --> 25:07.039
YOU HAVE A TREMENDOUS GIFT,
NEAL.

25:07.073 --> 25:10.242
YOUR ORIGINAL WORK
MUST BE EXTRAORDINARY.

25:10.276 --> 25:13.813
I DON'T HAVE
MANY ORIGINAL PIECES.

25:13.846 --> 25:14.747
WHY NOT?

25:17.383 --> 25:18.685
I DON'T KNOW.

25:18.718 --> 25:20.519
WELL, THAT'S A SHAME.

25:20.553 --> 25:23.656
BECAUSE IF YOU CAN
DO THIS...

25:23.690 --> 25:25.457
YOU'RE CAPABLE OF ANYTHING.

25:33.265 --> 25:34.533
ALL RIGHT,
HERE'S MY PROPOSAL --

25:34.567 --> 25:38.004
WE FINISH "COURTSHIP,"
SPLIT THE PROFITS 50/50.

25:38.037 --> 25:41.774
WELL, LET'S BE CLEAR --
FORGERY IS A FEDERAL OFFENSE.

25:43.375 --> 25:46.613
THIS IS
A DUBOIS REPLICA.

25:46.646 --> 25:48.414
UNDERSTOOD.

25:54.553 --> 25:57.256
THE CONTOURS AND PLANES
COMPLEMENT EACH OTHER WELL.

25:57.289 --> 25:58.190
I'M IMPRESSED.

25:58.224 --> 26:00.492
A SHAME
I HAVE TO DESTROY IT.

26:01.961 --> 26:03.763
WHAT'S THE POINT
OF MAKING A REPLICA

26:03.796 --> 26:05.431
OF A PIECE
YOU'VE ALREADY SOLD?

26:09.902 --> 26:13.572
DUBOIS USED TO SAY, "DON'T GET
ATTACHED TO YOUR WORK."

26:13.606 --> 26:15.341
[ STONE CLATTERING ]

26:17.409 --> 26:21.213
NEAL'S FIGURED OUT A WAY
TO NAIL BELLMIERE ON FORGERY.

26:21.247 --> 26:22.915
YOU PROMISED ME
A CONFESSION.

26:22.949 --> 26:24.984
NOW I'M PROMISING YOU
HARD EVIDENCE.

26:25.017 --> 26:26.552
[ SIGHS ]
KEEP TALKING.

26:26.585 --> 26:28.587
DUBOIS PUT AN ORIGINAL,
HAND-WRITTEN NOTE

26:28.621 --> 26:30.289
INTO THE HEART
OF EACH PIECE.

26:30.322 --> 26:32.591
YES, I KNOW. THE TIBEDAUX
X-RAYED IT AND FOUND IT.

26:32.625 --> 26:35.294
THE X-RAY ONLY VERIFIED ITS
EXISTENCE, NOT WHAT WAS ON IT.

26:35.327 --> 26:36.929
YEAH,
IF THE SCROLL CONTAINS

26:36.963 --> 26:38.965
BELLMIERE'S HANDWRITING
AND FINGERPRINTS

26:38.998 --> 26:41.100
AND NOT DUBOIS',
THEN IT'S A FORGERY.

26:41.133 --> 26:43.569
WHAT ARE YOU SUGGESTING?
THAT WE SMASH IT OPEN?

26:43.602 --> 26:44.904
WELL,
THERE'S PROBABLY A --

26:44.937 --> 26:46.438
FORTUNATELY,
WE HAVE ANOTHER OPTION.

26:50.176 --> 26:52.244
A HIGH-RESOLUTION
IMAGING SCANNER.

26:52.278 --> 26:54.446
THE NEW MAGNETIC
TOMOGRAPHY SCANNERS

26:54.480 --> 26:56.415
ARE PORTABLE
AND POWERFUL ENOUGH

26:56.448 --> 26:59.418
TO PICK UP FINGERPRINTS ON A GUN
THROUGH A BRICK WALL.

26:59.451 --> 27:01.153
IT'S STILL NEAL'S WORD
AGAINST BELLMIERE'S.

27:01.187 --> 27:02.989
I DON'T THINK A JUDGE IS GONNA
APPROVE A WARRANT.

27:03.022 --> 27:03.923
WE DON'T NEED ONE.

27:03.956 --> 27:05.457
YOU HAVE
A CONFIDENTIAL INFORMANT

27:05.491 --> 27:07.860
WHO HAS ACCESS
TO THE SCULPTURE.

27:10.529 --> 27:12.631
ALL RIGHT.

27:12.665 --> 27:14.300
BUT I'M GONNA GO WITH YOU --
I'M GONNA OVERSEE THIS.

27:14.333 --> 27:16.302
AND IT'S NOT BECAUSE
I DON'T TRUST YOU, PETER.

27:16.335 --> 27:18.437
IT'S BECAUSE
I DON'T TRUST HIM.

27:18.470 --> 27:21.607
YOU SAID THIS WAS A HIGH-PROFILE
CASE, AND YOU'RE RIGHT.

27:21.640 --> 27:23.943
I WANT A CLEAN CONVICTION,
NO DETOURS.

27:23.976 --> 27:25.311
HAVE YOU GOT IT, NEAL?

27:25.344 --> 27:27.346
HE'S GOT IT.
I DIDN'T ASK YOU,
PETER.

27:27.379 --> 27:29.215
GOT IT.

27:29.248 --> 27:30.316
OKAY, GREAT.

27:30.349 --> 27:33.085
THEN WE SHOULDN'T HAVE
ANY PROBLEM.

27:36.155 --> 27:38.290
I KNOW THAT LOOK.
I DON'T LIKE THAT LOOK.

27:38.324 --> 27:39.959
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

27:39.992 --> 27:42.228
I KNOW HOW WE CAN FIND THE BOX
IN THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

27:42.261 --> 27:43.362
THE SCANNER.

27:43.395 --> 27:44.330
YEAH.
NO.

27:44.363 --> 27:47.734
THAT LITTLE DEVICE
IS WORTH A SMALL DUBOIS.

27:47.767 --> 27:49.736
I CAN'T JUST CHECK IT OUT
LIKE A LIBRARY BOOK.

27:49.769 --> 27:52.238
I'LL USE IT WHILE I'M SUPPOSED
TO BE IN BELLMIERE'S LOFT.

27:52.271 --> 27:53.906
DID YOU MISS THE PART
ABOUT NO DETOURS?

27:53.940 --> 27:55.908
CALLAWAY'S GONNA BE
IN THE VAN.

27:55.942 --> 27:57.543
OKAY, THERE YOU GO.
THANKS.

27:57.576 --> 28:00.379
I'M NOT GONNA JEOPARDIZE
OUR FIRST OPERATION.

28:00.412 --> 28:02.014
SHE WON'T KNOW A THING.

28:02.048 --> 28:03.716
THIS IS NOT
A WINK AND A NOD.

28:03.750 --> 28:04.817
NO.

28:04.851 --> 28:06.719
I HEAR YOU.

28:06.753 --> 28:08.320
I DON'T THINK YOU DO.
WHAT?

28:08.354 --> 28:11.223
I NEED YOU TO SAY,
"I WILL NOT USE THE SCANNER

28:11.257 --> 28:12.759
TO SEARCH
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING."

28:12.792 --> 28:14.426
I WILL NOT USE THE SCANNER

28:14.460 --> 28:16.428
TO SEARCH
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

28:16.462 --> 28:18.197
"OR MOZZIE OR JAMES."

28:18.230 --> 28:20.032
NEITHER I,
NOR MOZZIE, NOR JAMES

28:20.066 --> 28:22.234
WILL USE THE SCANNER
FOR SUCH A SEARCH.

28:23.402 --> 28:24.536
LITTLE PINKY-SWEAR ACTION?

28:28.074 --> 28:30.209
MOZ,
MEET ME AT MY PLACE.

28:30.242 --> 28:43.522
I GOT A WAY
TO FIND THE EVIDENCE.

28:43.555 --> 28:46.458
HERE IS YOUR SURVEILLANCE WATCH
DU JOUR.

28:46.492 --> 28:50.296
THIS IS ONE AN ARTISAN
MIGHT WEAR WHILE SCULPTING.

28:50.329 --> 28:52.131
KEEP THOSE UPGRADES
COMING.

28:52.164 --> 28:56.135
AUDIO'S GOOD.
I'VE CALIBRATED THE SCANNER.

28:56.168 --> 28:57.303
CAREFUL.

28:57.336 --> 28:59.105
I'LL KEEP IT SAFE.

28:59.138 --> 28:59.906
ANKLET.

28:59.939 --> 29:01.740
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

29:01.774 --> 29:04.276
NO.
LET'S LEAVE IT ON.

29:04.310 --> 29:07.213
THIS IS
AN UNDERCOVER OPERATION.

29:07.246 --> 29:09.481
BELLMIERE'S AN ART FORGER.
HE'S NOT AIRPORT SECURITY.

29:09.515 --> 29:11.150
HE WON'T BE
PATTING CAFFREY DOWN.

29:11.183 --> 29:13.085
STANDARD PROCEDURE
IS TO REMOVE THE ANKLET.

29:13.119 --> 29:14.453
WE'RE LESS THAN
500 YARDS AWAY,

29:14.486 --> 29:16.889
AND WE'VE EARS ON HIM
WITH THE WATCH.

29:16.923 --> 29:19.758
WOULD YOU STAND UP?

29:19.792 --> 29:21.260
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

29:28.634 --> 29:31.470
THERE. YOU'RE
A VERY TALENTED CON ARTIST.

29:31.503 --> 29:33.272
YOU'LL FIGURE OUT
HOW TO KEEP THAT COVERED.

29:33.305 --> 29:34.606
NO PROBLEM.

29:40.980 --> 29:43.182
Mozzie: WELL,
THE VIEWS ARE IMPRESSIVE.

29:43.215 --> 29:45.317
THIS HIGH UP
IN THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING --

29:45.351 --> 29:47.253
LOCATION IS EVERYTHING.

29:47.286 --> 29:50.189
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I TELL MY CUSTOMERS --

29:50.222 --> 29:52.291
I RUN AN ICE-CREAM
FRANCHISE.

29:54.326 --> 29:56.328
SECURITY WAS A BEAR
GETTING UP HERE.

29:56.362 --> 29:58.430
YEAH. METAL DETECTORS
IN THE LOBBY,

29:58.464 --> 30:00.366
CAMERAS AT THE ENTRIES
AND EXITS,

30:00.399 --> 30:03.302
VISITOR REGISTRATION
AND ACCESS-CONTROL SYSTEMS.

30:03.335 --> 30:05.938
CHECK-IN DESK EVERY FLOOR --
IT'S VERY SAFE.

30:05.972 --> 30:08.207
OH, YEAH.
I CAN IMAGINE.

30:09.308 --> 30:12.644
IT WOULD BE NEXT TO IMPOSSIBLE
TO SNEAK UP, LIKE,

30:12.678 --> 30:14.180
A -- I DON'T KNOW --

30:14.213 --> 30:16.315
A METAL...SCANNER
OR SOMETHING.

30:16.348 --> 30:17.549
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

30:17.583 --> 30:19.618
NOW,
THAT OFFICE IS DIRECTLY BELOW.

30:19.651 --> 30:21.553
DOES THAT POSE
ANY NOISE PROBLEMS?

30:21.587 --> 30:22.521
NO.

30:22.554 --> 30:23.689
THEY'VE GOT
20-FOOT CEILINGS,

30:23.722 --> 30:25.958
AND WE'VE GOT THREE INCHES
OF MARBLE --

30:25.992 --> 30:29.328
I THINK YOU HAVE SOMETHING
ON YOUR SHOE.

30:31.097 --> 30:32.198
OH, MY.

30:32.231 --> 30:33.399
[ SCOFFS ]

30:33.432 --> 30:36.235
OH, MY.
I AM SO SORRY.

30:36.268 --> 30:37.469
[ SIGHS ]

30:37.503 --> 30:39.805
W-WHAT IS THIS?

30:39.838 --> 30:42.541
NO -- STOP.

30:42.574 --> 30:44.410
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

30:44.443 --> 30:45.477
[ Cellphone speed-dialing ]

30:45.511 --> 30:46.812
YEAH, HI.

30:46.845 --> 30:52.251
I'M GONNA NEED THE MARBLE BUFFED
ON THE RENTAL FLOOR.

30:52.284 --> 30:53.752
NO.

30:53.785 --> 30:58.224
THIS AFTERNOON --
BEFORE THE NEXT SHOWING.

30:58.257 --> 30:59.358
THANKS.

30:59.391 --> 31:01.693
OY.

31:05.597 --> 31:07.599
ALL RIGHT.

31:11.703 --> 31:15.341
LISTEN, IF YOU DON'T MIND.
I LIKE TO WORK ALONE.

31:15.374 --> 31:17.309
JUST...PART OF MY PROCESS.

31:20.112 --> 31:22.381
I'M THE SAME WAY.

31:22.414 --> 31:24.917
I'M GONNA GO GRAB
SOME COFFEE.

31:47.173 --> 31:49.008
[ CHISEL CLINKING ]

32:09.528 --> 32:10.696
[ CLINKING CONTINUES ]

32:15.867 --> 32:20.439
I ALWAYS WONDERED
WHEN WE'D GO OUT FOR ICE CREAM.

32:20.472 --> 32:24.276
MOZZIE CALLS IT
"MINT CHOCOLATE TRACKING CHIP."

32:24.310 --> 32:26.612
ALL RIGHT,
I RE-SET THE SCANNER

32:26.645 --> 32:29.348
SO THAT THE TRACKING SIGNAL
WON'T REACH THE VAN.

32:31.383 --> 32:34.353
PERFECT.

32:34.386 --> 32:37.689
AH, HERE COMES
OUR CUSTODIAL ACCOMPLICE.

32:43.529 --> 32:45.764
HARV'S THE MAN
THEY CALL.

32:45.797 --> 32:46.832
IS HE O.C.D.?

32:46.865 --> 32:48.834
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT MAKES HIM
SO THOROUGH.

32:48.867 --> 32:52.204
LOVES DOGS.
HAS A NIECE NAMED DAISY, RIGHT?
YOU GOT IT.

32:52.238 --> 32:53.339
[ CHUCKLES ] 'SCUSE ME!

32:53.372 --> 32:55.474
'SCUSE ME.
YEAH?

32:55.507 --> 32:57.476
[ Panting ] UH, SORRY
TO BOTHER YOU, BUT YOU...

32:57.509 --> 32:59.178
YOU SEEN A COLLIE
RUN BY HERE,

32:59.211 --> 33:02.548
ABOUT YEA BIG,
GOT A MAGNIFICENT BROWN COAT?

33:02.581 --> 33:04.316
GOES BY THE NAME OF DAISY?

33:04.350 --> 33:05.351
OH, NO. DAISY?
YEAH.

33:05.384 --> 33:06.318
THAT'S MY NIECE'S NAME.

33:06.352 --> 33:07.519
NO KIDDING?
YEAH.

33:07.553 --> 33:08.987
WELL, I WAS WALKING HER
DOWN FIFTH AVENUE.

33:09.021 --> 33:10.889
SHE JUST UP AND RAN AWAY.
JUST BOLTED -- JUST RAN AWAY.

33:10.922 --> 33:12.291
DOES SHE HAVE TAGS?

33:12.324 --> 33:14.526
'COURSE SHE'S GOT TAGS!
YOU SURE YOU HAVEN'T SEEN HER?

33:14.560 --> 33:15.627
NO,
I HAVEN'T SEEN HER.

33:15.661 --> 33:16.862
NO? OH, MAN!

33:16.895 --> 33:19.331
WHAT A DAY TO FORGET
MY [Chuckling] GLASSES!

33:19.365 --> 33:20.766
[ CLINKING CONTINUES ]

33:25.404 --> 33:26.872
THIS COULD TAKE A WHILE.

33:26.905 --> 33:29.741
I KNOW HOW BUSY YOU ARE.
YOU DON'T NEED TO STAY.

33:29.775 --> 33:33.145
OH, I STARTED IN THE FIELD.
I LIKE BEING OUT HERE.

33:33.179 --> 33:34.546
ME, TOO.

33:34.580 --> 33:35.381
MM.

33:46.725 --> 33:48.427
James:
IT'S BEEN 45 MINUTES.

33:48.460 --> 33:50.529
HOW DO YOU KNOW WHEN WE'VE
SCANNED THE BOX?

33:50.562 --> 33:53.399
Neal: WE WON'T UNTIL WE TAKE IT
BACK AND MATCH THE RESULTS

33:53.432 --> 33:55.867
TO THE FLOOR PLANS
AND THE DIMENSIONS OF THE BOX.

33:55.901 --> 33:58.104
YOU GUYS EVER RUN
A CON LIKE THIS BEFORE?

33:58.137 --> 33:59.871
CAN'T SAY
I'VE EVER USED A BUFFER

33:59.905 --> 34:01.973
TO RUN AN X-RAY SCANNER
ACROSS A FLOOR.

34:03.975 --> 34:05.411
THAT DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

34:06.978 --> 34:09.548
UH-OH. WE'RE HAVING
A TECHNICAL DIFFICULTY.

34:11.783 --> 34:13.519
THE IMAGE IS BREAKING UP.

34:13.552 --> 34:14.386
WE LOST IT.

34:14.420 --> 34:16.355
HE FINISHED 90%
OF THE FLOOR.

34:16.388 --> 34:18.890
LET'S HOPE THE BOX
IS IN THERE SOMEWHERE.

34:18.924 --> 34:21.127
THAT SCANNER
HAS TO BE COMPLETELY INTACT

34:21.160 --> 34:22.494
WHEN I RETURN IT TO THE FBI.

34:27.599 --> 34:30.068
[ CLINKING CONTINUES ]

34:30.102 --> 34:31.270
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

34:31.303 --> 34:33.805
I'M CHECKING ON CAFFREY.
SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT.

34:33.839 --> 34:35.040
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

34:35.073 --> 34:37.042
YOU'RE PULLING UP
HIS TRACKING DATA?

34:37.075 --> 34:38.210
WE CAN HEAR HIM.

34:38.244 --> 34:40.612
WE CAN HEAR CHISELING.
WE CAN'T HEAR HIM.

34:40.646 --> 34:41.947
I CAN'T TELL YOU WHY,

34:41.980 --> 34:43.515
BUT I GET THE FEELING
CAFFREY'S UP TO SOMETHING.

34:46.418 --> 34:47.486
DENIED.

34:47.519 --> 34:49.255
I.T. MUST NOT HAVE ACTIVATED
YOUR I.D. YET.

34:49.288 --> 34:50.789
TYPE IN YOURS.

34:50.822 --> 34:53.592
OKAY.

35:13.445 --> 35:16.482
HMM.
MUST HAVE MADE A TYPO.

35:18.450 --> 35:22.188
I'M PULLING IT UP RIGHT NOW.

35:28.794 --> 35:30.329
RIGHT WHERE
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

35:30.362 --> 35:32.364
[ CLANKING CONTINUES ]

36:04.563 --> 36:07.666
ALL RIGHT, BELLMIERE'S GONE.
I'M SCANNING NOW.

36:14.440 --> 36:17.409
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

36:17.443 --> 36:18.710
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36:20.446 --> 36:22.548
OH, I WAS JUST...LOOKING
AT YOUR HANDIWORK AGAIN.

36:22.581 --> 36:25.251
DUBOIS' HANDIWORK.

36:25.284 --> 36:27.152
STICK TO THE ONES IN BACK.

36:27.185 --> 36:28.387
ALL RIGHT.

36:30.456 --> 36:31.557
HERE IT IS.

36:34.593 --> 36:36.528
THE CALIBRATION'S OFF.
IT'S COMPLETELY UNREADABLE.

36:36.562 --> 36:38.297
YEAH,
I'M PULLING HIM OUT OF HERE.

36:39.298 --> 36:40.432
[ CELLPHONE BUZZES ]

36:52.411 --> 36:55.046
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

36:55.080 --> 36:57.249
I'M GONNA GET
SOME FRESH AIR.

37:00.652 --> 37:02.521
[ BAG CLANGS ]

37:02.554 --> 37:03.822
YOU KNOW WHAT?

37:05.324 --> 37:07.359
THE INITIAL CARVING
ISN'T WORKING FOR ME.

37:07.393 --> 37:10.128
THAT'S EXACTLY HOW I DID IT
FOR DUBOIS.

37:10.161 --> 37:11.463
DIDN'T YOU TELL HIM
TO ABORT?

37:11.497 --> 37:13.532
HE WAS HAPPY WITH THAT?
YEAH.

37:13.565 --> 37:15.301
BUT HE NEVER LET YOU
FINISH ONE.

37:15.334 --> 37:17.102
HE OBSESSED
OVER EVERY DETAIL.

37:17.135 --> 37:18.770
YEAH,
AND HE MADE YOU START OVER --

37:18.804 --> 37:21.940
SEVERAL TIMES,
IF I RECALL.

37:21.973 --> 37:23.475
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

37:23.509 --> 37:26.945
OH, I DO.
I WENT THROUGH HIS NOTES.

37:26.978 --> 37:29.080
HE DIDN'T WANT TO DESTROY
HIS WORK.

37:29.114 --> 37:31.216
YOU LEFT HIM NO CHOICE.

37:31.249 --> 37:33.218
HE HAD TO START OVER
BECAUSE YOU WEREN'T GOOD ENOUGH.

37:33.251 --> 37:36.087
OH, PLEASE.
HE NEVER KNEW WHAT HE WANTED.

37:36.121 --> 37:37.923
HE'D START OVER...20 TIMES.

37:37.956 --> 37:39.791
HE'D BLOW EVERYTHING UP
AT THE LAST MINUTE

37:39.825 --> 37:40.892
AND LEAVE ME TO FIX IT!

37:40.926 --> 37:41.927
I MADE HIM WHAT HE IS!

37:44.830 --> 37:46.998
WHENEVER YOU LOOK AT A DUBOIS,
YOU'RE LOOKIN' AT ME.

37:47.032 --> 37:48.534
THEN WHY ISN'T YOUR NAME
ON IT?

37:50.268 --> 37:51.470
Callaway:
GET HIM OUT OF THERE!

37:51.503 --> 37:53.238
HE'S GOING
FOR A CONFESSION.

37:53.271 --> 37:56.342
YOU HIDE BEHIND HIS WORK,
YOU LIVE OFF HIS NAME,

37:56.375 --> 37:58.577
BUT WITHOUT DUBOIS,
YOU'RE NOTHING.

37:58.610 --> 37:59.611
YOU DON'T EXIST.

38:01.680 --> 38:03.014
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

38:05.216 --> 38:06.251
LET'S MOVE.

38:06.284 --> 38:07.986
I'LL MONITOR FROM HERE.

38:09.521 --> 38:11.723
[ GRUNTING CONTINUES ]

38:15.494 --> 38:16.628
Diana: FBI!

38:16.662 --> 38:18.430
DROP IT!
DROP THAT WEAPON!

38:18.464 --> 38:20.466
OKAY! OKAY!
THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE.

38:20.499 --> 38:22.601
THIS CON ARTIST,
NEAL CAFFREY,

38:22.634 --> 38:24.503
JUST BROKE
A $10 MILLION SCULPTURE.

38:24.536 --> 38:26.171
[ Panting ] IT'S A FAKE.
I CAN PROVE IT.

38:26.204 --> 38:27.739
RIGHT THERE.

38:36.648 --> 38:40.386
I STAND CORRECTED.
YOUEXIST.

38:40.419 --> 38:41.853
Peter: YOU ONCE TOLD ME
EVERY FORGER

38:41.887 --> 38:44.155
FINDS A WAY
TO SIGN HIS OWN NAME.

38:44.189 --> 38:47.693
MR. BLATNIK, WHY DON'T YOU COME
WITH US TO THE BUREAU?

38:47.726 --> 38:49.628
THE SAD THING IS,

38:49.661 --> 38:51.563
YOU'RE MORE TALENTED
THAN DUBOIS.

39:05.744 --> 39:07.746
I WONDER HOW THIS SCANNER
GOT SO SCRATCHED UP.

39:07.779 --> 39:09.681
MUST HAVE FALLEN OUT OF
MY POCKET WHEN HE ATTACKED ME.

39:09.715 --> 39:10.582
MM.

39:24.530 --> 39:26.097
HEY.

39:26.131 --> 39:27.699
HEY.

39:27.733 --> 39:28.900
HOW'D IT GO?

39:28.934 --> 39:31.202
OH, FORENSICS CONFIRMED
IT WAS A FORGERY,

39:31.236 --> 39:33.739
AS WELL AS THE ONE HE SOLD
AT THE TIBEDAUX.

39:33.772 --> 39:36.942
THAT'S GREAT, BUT I WAS TALKING
ABOUT THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

39:36.975 --> 39:38.544
WE FOUND IT.

39:40.479 --> 39:41.413
YOU FOUND IT?

39:41.447 --> 39:43.549
MOZZIE FOUND
A RECTANGULAR OBJECT

39:43.582 --> 39:46.618
THE EXACT DIMENSIONS
OF ELLEN'S EVIDENCE BOX

39:46.652 --> 39:48.454
ON THE SOUTHWEST SIDE
OF THE CEILING.

39:48.487 --> 39:50.756
[ Laughing ] WELL,
LET'S GO GET IT!
NO, THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO TONIGHT.

39:50.789 --> 39:52.458
IT'S NOT EASY ACCESS.

39:52.491 --> 39:54.960
WELL,
DOES PETER KNOW?
NO, NOT YET.
I'LL TELL HIM TOMORROW.

39:54.993 --> 39:56.595
WELL, NOW THAT WE KNOW
WHERE IT IS,

39:56.628 --> 39:58.597
LET ME GO GET IT,
KEEP YOU TWO GUYS CLEAN.

39:58.630 --> 40:01.099
NO,
I CAN'T DO THAT TO PETER.

40:01.132 --> 40:02.701
WELL,
YOU JUST RAN A CON ON HIM.

40:02.734 --> 40:03.969
I'M NOT DOING THIS
WITHOUT HIM.

40:04.002 --> 40:06.304
LISTEN, YOU PROMISED ME
THAT YOU WEREN'T GONNA DO THIS.

40:06.337 --> 40:08.574
HE'S BEEN MORE OF A FATHER TO ME
THAN YOU EVER WERE.

40:12.243 --> 40:14.412
WE'RE DOING THIS
WITH PETER.

40:16.147 --> 40:19.150
OKAY. YOU'RE RIGHT.

40:21.286 --> 40:25.256
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

40:25.290 --> 40:28.126
YOU ASKED ME WHY I DON'T HAVE
ORIGINAL ART?

40:28.159 --> 40:30.428
I'VE HAD
THREE DIFFERENT NAMES

40:30.462 --> 40:32.531
AND A DOZEN DIFFERENT ALIASES
BECAUSE OF YOU.

40:34.766 --> 40:38.336
AND TO BE AN ARTIST,
YOU HAVE TO KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

40:38.369 --> 40:42.340
YOU'RE MY SON.

40:42.373 --> 40:44.175
AND I'M VERY PROUD OF THAT.

40:55.854 --> 40:58.757
YOU KNOW, NEAL WAS
CHISELING AWAY FOR A LONG TIME,

40:58.790 --> 41:01.326
BUT I NEVER ACTUALLY SAW
ANY CARVING IN EVIDENCE.

41:01.359 --> 41:02.694
I'M SURE THERE'S A REASON.

41:02.728 --> 41:04.429
YOU BOTH AGREED --
NO DETOURS.

41:04.462 --> 41:06.598
[ SIGHS ] WE DID.

41:06.632 --> 41:09.535
I GET IT NOW.

41:09.568 --> 41:10.769
WHAT'S THAT?

41:10.802 --> 41:14.372
WHY HUGHES APPROVED SO MANY
OF YOUR UNORTHODOX OPERATIONS.

41:14.405 --> 41:15.674
REALLY?

41:15.707 --> 41:17.843
YOU GAVE ME A BIG WIN,
BUT I DON'T NEED ANYONE

41:17.876 --> 41:19.845
LOOKING INTO WHATEVER IT WAS
CAFFREY WAS DOING.

41:19.878 --> 41:21.513
[ Chuckling ]
I'M SURE IT'S NOT THAT BAD.

41:21.547 --> 41:22.614
PETER.

41:22.648 --> 41:24.816
IS ANY OF THIS
GONNA BLOW BACK ON ME?

41:24.850 --> 41:26.217
NO.

41:26.251 --> 41:28.319
LET'S KEEP IT THAT WAY.

41:28.353 --> 41:30.488
YOU CONTINUE TO GIVE ME
MORE WINS,

41:30.522 --> 41:33.158
AND I WILL GIVE YOUR TEAM
EVERYTHING IT NEEDS.

41:33.191 --> 41:34.492
WIN-WIN.

41:38.764 --> 41:40.566
AGENT WATSON,
DID YOU FIND ANYTHING?

41:40.599 --> 41:43.068
SCANNER'S DAMAGED
PRETTY BADLY.

41:43.101 --> 41:45.871
I SEE THAT.

41:45.904 --> 41:47.806
AND SCRUBBED DATA
OFF THE HARD DRIVE.

41:47.839 --> 41:49.040
WERE YOU ABLE TO RECOVER
ANY OF IT?

41:49.074 --> 41:50.241
ABOUT 20%.

41:50.275 --> 41:53.845
WHOEVER USED THE SCANNER
WAS SEARCHING A BUILDING.

41:53.879 --> 41:56.782
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

41:58.516 --> 41:59.551
IS THAT A SERIAL NUMBER?

41:59.585 --> 42:01.386
YEP.
IT'S A CABLE JUNCTION BOX.

42:01.419 --> 42:04.155
THIS PARTICULAR MODEL
WAS USED IN ONLY ONE PLACE --

42:04.189 --> 42:06.992
FLOORS 33 TO 61
OF THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

42:07.025 --> 42:09.695
THANKS, AGENT WATSON.

42:09.728 --> 42:11.429
THANK YOU.

42:11.462 --> 42:12.898
OH, WILL YOU SHUT THE DOOR
ON YOUR WAY OUT?

42:17.703 --> 42:19.738
[ Dialing ]

42:19.771 --> 42:23.241
[ Ringing ]

42:23.274 --> 42:24.843
SENATOR PRATT, PLEASE.

42:24.876 --> 42:26.645
AMANDA CALLAWAY.

42:32.818 --> 42:35.420
I THINK
I MAY HAVE YOUR ANSWER.
